usage: event-create [-h] [-l {debug,info,warning,error,critical}]
                    [-a api_host] [-e e_mail] [-t api_token] [-z]
                    [-b {acknowledged,closed,ok,open}] [-c EVENT_CLASS]
                    [-r {info,warn,error,critical}] [-m message] -f field_list
                    [-o tenant_id] [-p property=value]
                    [-s ref:type:name:properties] -w title

Creates a new event in an TrueSight Pulse account

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -l {debug,info,warning,error,critical}, --log-level {debug,info,warning,error,critical}
                        Sets logging level to one of
                        debug,info,warning,error,critical. Default is logging
                        is disabled
  -a api_host, --api-host api_host
                        TrueSight Pulse API host endpoint
  -e e_mail, --email e_mail
                        e-mail that has access to the TrueSight Pulse account
  -t api_token, --api-token api_token
                        API token for given e-mail that has access to the
                        TrueSight Pulse account
  -z, --curl            Output the corresponding curl command line and exit
  -b {acknowledged,closed,ok,open}, --status {acknowledged,closed,ok,open}
  -c EVENT_CLASS, --event-class EVENT_CLASS
                        Event class of this event
  -r {info,warn,error,critical}, --severity {info,warn,error,critical}
                        Severity of the the event
  -m message, --message message
                        Text describing the event
  -f field_list, --fingerprint-fields field_list
                        List of fields that make up the fingerprint
  -o tenant_id, --tenant-id tenant_id
                        Tenant Id
  -p property=value, --property property=value
                        Add properties to an event
  -s ref:type:name:properties, --source ref:type:name:properties
                        A description or resolution of the alarm
  -w title, --title title
                        Title of the event
